overview: The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul for their sleep
  questionnaire app, aiming to move beyond its generic appearance. The assistant
  responded by implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color palette featuring
  indigos, purples, and teal accents, defined using OKLCH for perceptual
  uniformity. The main form layout was significantly redesigned, incorporating
  subtle background blurs, a modern progress indicator, and a unique star
  pattern overlay on card headers. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and cards were meticulously polished with improved sizing,
  transitions, and interactive hover/selected states. The IntroSection was
  transformed into a welcoming hero experience with engaging feature cards. A
  critical step involved applying consistent, themed card-style groupings across
  all 14 questionnaire sections, replacing previous generic gray boxes. The
  Report section's inconsistent hardcoded gradient headers and various gray
  text/background colors were also aligned with the new theme. Additionally, a
  React console error concerning  values in input components was resolved
  by safely converting  to an empty string within the  component.
  The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional, and calming application that
  significantly enhances the user experience.
